The advertising dataset contains information about users and their interaction with online ads. It includes features such as age, 
daily time spent on a website, area income, and daily internet usage, along with demographic details like city, country, and gender. The target variable,
“Clicked on Ad,” indicates whether a user clicked on an advertisement. This dataset is commonly used for classification tasks, 
especially logistic regression, to predict user behavior. By analyzing patterns in user activity and demographics, 
it helps identify key factors influencing ad engagement and supports building predictive models for digital marketing strategies.
